6.ADLS Gen1 vs ADLS Gen2?
ADLS Gen1 was Microsoft's first-generation data lake service designed specifically for big data analytics. It was a separate storage platform with support for hierarchical directories and analytics workloads. ADLS Gen2 is the successor and is built on top of Azure Blob Storage. By enabling Hierarchical Namespace, Blob Storage gains file-system capabilities such as directories, ACLs, and efficient rename and move operations. ADLS Gen2 provides better integration with the Azure ecosystem, supports both storage and analytics workloads, and is the recommended solution for modern Azure Data Lake implementations.

